"""macli — macos-cli unified router.

Three top-level namespaces, all dispatched from this single file:

  macli x  <cmd> [args...]     X/Twitter ops (twitter-cli + bird + opencli)
  macli wx <cmd> [args...]     WeChat ops (vendor/wechat-mcp, locally patched)
  macli mac <cmd> [args...]    macOS apps + system (osascript + 492 KB scripts)

Plus a legacy passthrough: any unrecognized first token routes to the X
subsystem so old magpie users can keep typing `macli search "..."` directly.

Architecture: single 1200-LOC Python file. No pip dependencies. WeChat ops
delegate to vendor/wechat-mcp's venv Python (pyobjc requirement).

Originally magpie (https://github.com/BuddhaYi/magpie) was a separate
project; v0.2 absorbed its full routing logic for a true single-file CLI.
"""

